</div><div title="dosage-of-meloxicam-for-dogs-side-effects" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-gIBqdA biKLcv pf-14_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0079/3287/0756/t/6/assets/pf-7aef199c--dosageofmeloxicamfordogssideeffects_1200x.jpg?v=1618072781" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0079/3287/0756/t/6/assets/pf-7aef199c--dosageofmeloxicamfordogssideeffects.jpg?v=1618072781 1536w" width="905" height="408" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="dosage-of-meloxicam-for-dogs-side-effects" title="dosage-of-meloxicam-for-dogs-side-effects"/></div><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-15_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-16_"><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-17_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-19_">You can feel the stiffness creep into your body as you watch your best friend hobble. Your pup is in pain, but she keeps that beautiful smile on her face because she is happy to see you. The bond you have is unbreakable, but you miss the outdoor time you and the dog shared hiking, playing fetch, and seeing fur friends at the local dog parks. <br><br>Your girl was recently diagnosed with Osteoarthritis. The vet prescribed Meloxicam, a drug that can help her feel better and improve her quality of life. As with any new medication, you worry about several things that could go wrong.<br><br>This blog looks at Meloxicam's uses, safety, dosage, cost, side effects, and alternatives. 
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-20_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-22_">Table Of Contents</span></h3><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:1px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-edERGn TYgaU pf-23_"><li data-to-section="pf-48_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-24_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-26_">What is Meloxicam?<br></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-59_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-27_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-29_">What is Meloxicam used for in dogs?<br></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-68_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-30_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-32_">Is Meloxicam Safe for Dogs?<br></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-123_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-33_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-35_">Meloxicam Dosage for Dogs<br></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-134_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-36_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-38_">How Much Does Meloxicam Cost?<br></span></li><li data-to-section="pf-145_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-39_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-41_">Side Effects of Meloxicam</span></li><li data-to-section="pf-184_" data-offset="{&quot;all&quot;:50,&quot;laptop&quot;:50,&quot;tablet&quot;:50,&quot;mobile&quot;:50}" href="#" data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-42_ animate-backward"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-44_">Natural Alternatives</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-ac2a" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-45_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-46_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-47_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-48_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-50_">What is Meloxicam?<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-51_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-52_"><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-53_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-55_">Meloxicam is a medication that is used to relieve pain and inflammation in dogs with Osteoarthritis. It is very similar to the medication Mobic, which is used to treat pain and inflammation in people.<br>
<br>The FDA approved the use of Meloxicam for dogs as long as a veterinarian prescribes it.&nbsp;</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-6c86" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-56_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-57_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-58_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-59_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-61_">What is Meloxicam used for in dogs?<br></span></h2><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-62_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-64_">Veterinarians most commonly prescribe Meloxicam to treat dogs with inflammation, stiffness, and pain caused by Osteoarthritis. However, Meloxicam can also be used to treat symptoms of other bone and muscle disorders.<br><br>Meloxicam is a drug that helps reduce inflammation and pain in dogs. It does this without using steroids, which can have harmful side effects.<br><br>Additionally, vets prescribe Meloxicam to reduce pain in dogs. This drug is useful for treating both chronic and short-term conditions.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-d6e5" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-65_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-66_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-67_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-68_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-70_">Is Meloxicam Safe for Dogs?<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-71_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-72_"><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-73_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-75_">As mentioned earlier, the FDA has fully approved the use of Meloxicam for dogs. However, dog owners should still be careful when administering the drug.<br>
<br>You shouldn't use Meloxicam in the following situations:
</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-edERGn TYgaU pf-76_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-77_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-79_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets with bloody vomit&nbsp;</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-80_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-82_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets with kidney or liver conditions</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-83_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-85_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets experiencing a loss of appetite.</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-86_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-88_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Dehydrated pets</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-89_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-91_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets that are pregnant&nbsp;</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-92_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-94_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Pets younger than six months old</span><br></span></li></ul><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-95_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-97_">Meloxicam may have adverse effects when used with other medications. So it is important to talk to your vet and tell them about all the medications your pet is taking.<br><br>You should exercise caution when using Meloxicam with the following drugs:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-edERGn TYgaU pf-98_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-99_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-101_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Certain antibiotics</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-102_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-104_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Anesthetics</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-105_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-107_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Anticoagulants</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-108_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-110_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Diuretics</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-111_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-113_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Antifungals</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-114_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-116_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Immunosuppressive drugs&nbsp;</span><br></span></li></ul><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-117_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-119_">Depending on your dog's situation, you and your vet may need to monitor your dog closely before and after the start of meloxicam usage. You will most likely have to monitor liver and kidney function and other signs of gastrointestinal ulceration.
<br>
<br>Veterinarians often require annual blood tests for dogs taking Meloxicam.
<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-066e" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-120_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-121_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-122_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-123_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-125_">Meloxicam Dosage for Dogs<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-126_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-127_"><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-128_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-130_">You should always administer Meloxicam according to your veterinarian's instructions.<br><br>When you are not sure how much Meloxicam to give your dog, it is best to start with the lowest recommended dose. The typical recommended dosage for Meloxicam is around 0.09 milligrams per pound of your dog's body weight on the first day.<br><br>After the first treatment, all subsequent treatments should be given once a day. The dosage is about 0.045 milligrams per pound of your body weight.<br><br>If you forget to give your dog their Meloxicam, try to give it to them as soon as possible. If there is only a short amount of time until the next dose is due, just miss the dose and continue with the normal schedule. You should never give your pet two doses of Meloxicam at the same time. </span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-edb5" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-131_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-132_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-133_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-134_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-136_">How Much Does Meloxicam Cost?<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-137_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-138_"><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-139_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-141_">Generic Meloxicam can be found for around 50 cents per tablet. However, it is important to make sure that you are buying from a reputable supplier.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-68c8" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-142_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-143_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-JkixQ lbFEmW pf-144_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-avest eSTvWa pf-145_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-147_">Side Effects of Meloxicam<br></span></h2><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-148_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-hZpJaK kKyviF pf-149_"><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-150_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-152_">Almost all side effects associated with meloxicam use in dogs involve gastrointestinal upset, similar to all other NSAID medications. If symptoms persist or worsen, however, you should contact your veterinarian immediately. They may want to adjust the dosage or prescribe an alternative treatment.<br><br>Common side effects associated with Meloxicam include:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-edERGn TYgaU pf-153_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-154_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-156_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Black or bloody diarrhea</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-157_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-159_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Bloody vomit</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-160_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-162_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Increased thirst</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-163_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-165_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Fatigue</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-166_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-168_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Jaundice</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-169_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-171_"><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;"><a href="https://www.relievet.com/blogs/tips/home-remedies-for-dogs-with-skin-allergies-itchy" style="">Itchiness</a></span></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-172_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-174_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Abdominal discomfort</span><br></span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jlsrNB kxxXtk pf-175_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-177_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Behavioral changes</span><br></span></li></ul><p class="sc-hYQoXb koTnzq pf-178_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hGnimi cpnKBf pf-180_">Just as with humans, there is a risk that your dog may have an allergic reaction to a medication. If you see any signs of an allergic reaction, like redness, swelling, or itchiness, contact your vet immediately.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5a4d" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-bSqaIl hxsZTX pf-181_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hkgtus clVJp"><div class="sc-bBHHxi gGMCwe pf-182_ pf-